<div><h3>EDUC 190 - Learning Through Disability Studies </h3>  <p><hr>Learning Through Disability Studies explores various definitions and concepts of disability while criticizing current social practice for its willful exclusion of related subjects. We begin by closely examining &#8220;disability&#8221; and its various connotations, then look at its permutations in the contexts of the legal and medical systems, activism, gender/race/class, education, art and film, spirituality, incarceration, and everyday life before ending with more radical ways of thinking about disability.<br><br><strong>Corequisites:</strong> &#160;</p>

